NOTICE
======

Provenance
----------
This project interoperates with MATLAB(R) by compiling Julia functions into
MEX files, by way of an independent, clean-room implementation of the publicly
documented MATLAB C Matrix API (the `mx*` and `mex*` functions and the
`mxArray` type), derived solely from MathWorks' public API documentation. It
contains:

  * NO MathWorks header files (e.g. mex.h, matrix.h),
  * NO MathWorks source code, and
  * NO MathWorks binaries or libraries.

Mexicah.jl declares the MATLAB C API via `ccall` (without headers) and, through
LibMx.jl, generates and compiles MEX files. The shared mxArray FFI and
marshaling core lives in LibMx.jl. The purpose is interoperability, not the
reproduction of MATLAB or any of its components.

